data.description: Experience the history of NB with this incredible vintage home in the downtown area. An eclectic home on an oversized lot that has many unique features, partial original hardwood floors, beadboard ceiling, board and batten walls, vintage sliding barn doors. The addition of the primary bedroom offers an attached bath with concrete flooring. The kitchen is open to the family room and dining room & showcases a gas range, butcher block countertops, center island with a granite countertop, open shelving & oversized pantry. There are 2 additional guest bedrooms, an updated bathroom with a clawfoot tub. The large fenced backyard has the original 1920's house, there is plenty of room for a pool or entertaining. Dining, boutiques, art galleries, river recreation, parks, breweries, bars are all within walking distance. This is a rare opportunity to own a property in downtown New Braunfels.
